documentation.text: @notice Primary sale auction contract for MarketTrading NFTs
@notice Event emitted only on construction. To be used by indexers
@notice instagram URL -> highest bidder info (if a bid has been received)
@notice instagram URL -> Auction finished info
@notice NFT - the only NFT that can be auctioned in this contract
@notice responsible for enforcing admin access
@notice globally bid lock time, bidders can't withdraw bid before bidLockTime.
@notice globally and across all auctions, the amount by which a bid has to increase
@notice global platform fee, assumed to always be to 1 decimal place i.e. 50 = 5.0%
@notice global resell platform fee, assumed to always be to 1 decimal place i.e. 25 = 2.5%
@notice global creator fee, assumed to always be to 1 decimal place i.e. 100 = 10.0%
@notice global cancel fee, assumed to always be to 1 decimal place i.e. 50 = 5.0%
@notice where to send platform fee funds to
@notice for switching off auction creations, bids and withdrawals

NFTAuctionContractDeployed().notice: Event emitted only on construction. To be used by indexers

bidLockTime().notice: globally bid lock time, bidders can't withdraw bid before bidLockTime.

cancelFee().notice: global cancel fee, assumed to always be to 1 decimal place i.e. 50 = 5.0%

creatorFee().notice: global creator fee, assumed to always be to 1 decimal place i.e. 100 = 10.0%

getHighestBidder(string).notice: Method for getting all info about the highest bidder

highestBids(string).notice: instagram URL -> highest bidder info (if a bid has been received)

isPaused().notice: for switching off auction creations, bids and withdrawals

marketTradingNft().notice: NFT - the only NFT that can be auctioned in this contract

minBidIncrement().notice: globally and across all auctions, the amount by which a bid has to increase

placeBid(string).notice: Places a new bid, out bidding the existing bidder if found and criteria is reached

platformFee().notice: global platform fee, assumed to always be to 1 decimal place i.e. 50 = 5.0%

platformFeeRecipient().notice: where to send platform fee funds to

resellFee().notice: global resell platform fee, assumed to always be to 1 decimal place i.e. 25 = 2.5%

updateAccessControls(address).notice: Method for updating the access controls contract used by the NFT

updateBidLockTime(uint256).notice: Update the lock time of the higgest bid, before locktime passed the highest bidder can't cancel the auction

updateMinBidIncrement(uint256).notice: Update the amount by which bids have to increase, across all auctions

updatePlatformFeeRecipient(address).notice: Method for updating platform fee address

withdrawBid(string).notice: Given a sender who has the highest bid on a NFT, allows them to withdraw their bid

userdoc.notice: Primary sale auction contract for MarketTrading NFTs
